C(-3,8)
y=8/9x+4
\frac{8}{9}
(-3, 8)
 8 = \frac{8}{9} \cdot -3 + b 
 8 = -\frac{8}{3} + b 
 8 + \frac{8}{3} = b 
 y = \frac{8}{9} x + 8 + \frac{8}{3} 
 y - y_0 = m(x - x_0) 
 y - 8 = \frac{8}{9} (x - (-3)) 
 y - 8 = \frac{8}{9} (x + 3) 
 y = \frac{8}{9} x + \frac{8}{3} + 8 
y = mx + b;\;\;\;m = \text{slope}\tag{point-slope form}
