y=\dfrac 89 x+4 \implies m = \dfrac 89\tag{1}
m = \dfrac 89
(x_0 , y_0) = (-3,8)
(y - y_0) = m(x - x_0)\quad\quad\tag{(2): point-slope form}
y - 8 = \dfrac 89(x -(-3)) \iff y = \dfrac 89x + 8 + \dfrac{8}{3} \iff y = \frac 89x + 10 + \frac 23
\iff\quad y = \quad\dfrac 89 x + \dfrac{32}3 \quad= \quad\dfrac{8(x+12)}{9}
10 +\frac {2}3 - 4 = 6+\frac 23 = \frac{20}3
